[Tool]
Name: micropita
Repository: https://bitbucket.org/biobakery/micropita
Version(Tag): 1.1
Email: micropita-users@googlegroups.com
Webpage: www.huttenhower.sph.harvard.edu/micropita
Copyright: Timothy Tickle, Curtis Huttenhower
CopyrightYear: 2013
Dependencies: python (>= 2.7), r-base, python-matplotlib, python-numpy, python-scipy, python-mlpy, python-mpi4py, python-blist, python-cogent
Description(<60char): Two-stage microbial community sample selection.
Description(Longer): microPITA is a computational tool enabling sample selection in two-stage (tiered) studies. Using two-stage designs can more efficiently allocate resources, reducing study costs, and maximizing the use of samples.
CommandlineScripts: micropita/MicroPITA.py
PostInst: pip install biom-format
